__data__.text:
Karl Gorlami
564 Market Street,
San Francisco, 94 104,
United States
Apartment Info: Tiny apartment on the 1st floor. Green doors with ”KARL” written on them.
Date of Birth: 1920-10-01
Place of Birth: Paris, France
PERSONAL HISTORY
I was born in Paris, France. Lived there until the end of the 2nd World War. Post-war, I moved
to the USA and worked as a Lumberjack in California. I am now a retired lumberjack.
FAMILY MEMBERS
•Emilia La Baguette (Mother): My mother was a sweet and loving person, who always
listened to me. She unfortunately passed away in 1993. (Deceased)
•Monsieur Le Petit (Father): My father is a war hero who was killed during the second
world war in Italy. (Deceased)
•Caroline La Maison (Sister): My sister lives in NYC. We do not speak much. (Alive)
MEDICATION INFORMATION
•Aspirin: Once a day in the morning for headaches.
•Coricidin: Once a day in the morning for blood pressure.
•Xados: Once a day in the morning for allergies.
MEDICAL CONDITIONS
•Allergy to peanuts.
•High blood pressure.
•Occasional dizziness.
KEY AREAS OF ASSISTANCE
Groceries, Doctors, Relatives, Appointments, Navigation, Introduction.
MEMORY RESTORE TRIGGERS
Remember the first date with your sweetheart, Emily. It was in 1945 under the Eiffel Tower.
Right after the war had ended and everything was great.
EMERGENCY CONTACTS
Caroline La Maison (Sister): +1 888 555 1234
EMERGENCY PROCEDURES
Please contact my sister, Caroline La Maison, at +1 888 555 1234.
LOCATION OF LEGAL DOCUMENTS
All my documents are in the cupboard in the kitchen of my apartment.
